 :rootkit: /rootÂ´kit/, n. [very common] A kit for getting {root}; an
automated {cracking} tool. What {script kiddies} use. The existence of
rootkits means that large-scale attacks on insecure computers can be done by
people with no technical skills other than the ability to follow directions.
Rootkits designed to crack Microsoft operating systems and webservers are
especially common, because their software is so porous and easy to crack.